Requires

   POSIX environment
   Standard POSIX /bin/sh
   Some web client: curl | wget | lynx

   Perl - only on system wide install with manual pages

SYSTEM WIDE

   make install

MANUAL INSTALL

To install (as root)

   # Install without the *.sh extension.
   # System wide programs do not have extensions.

   install --mode=755 ddns-updater.sh /usr/local/bin/ddns-updater
   install --mode=644 cron.d/ddns-updater /etc/cron.d/

   mkdir --parents ~/.config/ddns-updater

Note:

  The configuration files can be installed in:

      $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/	   or
      /etc/ddns-updater/

Configure for duckdns.org

   # Copy TOKEN from your account page
   # SUBDOMAIN.duckdns.org

   $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/duckdns.conf
   DUCKDNS_TOKEN=token-string-here
   DUCKDNS_DOMAINS=subdomain,subdomain...

Configure for dns.he.net

   $HOME/.config/ddns-updater/henet.conf
   DUCKDNS_PASS=password
   DUCKDNS_DOMAINS=host.example.com
